# sports-analysis-project
A comprehensive beginner-friendly data analysis portfolio project that analyzes  basketball player statistics and creates professional visualizations. Demonstrates  proficiency in Python, Pandas data manipulation, statistical analysis, and  Matplotlib/Seaborn visualization. Includes detailed documentation.
#  Sports Statistics Analysis & Visualization

A beginner-friendly Python project demonstrating data analysis and visualization skills using real-world sports data.

## Project Overview

This project analyzes NBA player performance statistics and generates professional visualizations showing scoring trends, player comparisons, and statistical relationships.

### Sample Visualizations:
- **Top 10 Scorers** - Bar chart ranking players by points
- **Points vs Rebounds Analysis** - Scatter plot with assist indicators
- **Field Goal Percentage Distribution** - Histogram showing shooting efficiency
- **Height vs Scoring Correlation** - Trend analysis
- **Team Performance Comparison** - Multi-statistic team rankings

##  Key Features

 **Data Analysis with Pandas**
- Load, explore, and clean basketball statistics
- Filter, sort, and group data
- Calculate correlations and statistical insights

 **Professional Visualizations**
- Multiple chart types (bar, scatter, histogram, trend)
- Color-coded data with legends
- High-resolution export (300 DPI)

 **Well-Documented Code**
- Clear comments explaining each section
- Beginner-friendly structure
- Best practices demonstrated

 **Easy to Extend**
- Sample data included (no setup needed)
- Easy to swap with your own sports data
- Reusable functions for different datasets

